The paper analyzes the interactions of political candidates on Twitter, using complex network analysis and community detection algorithms to measure influence and relevance. This suggests a focus on social media and its impact on politics, which falls under the categories of social networks (cs.SI, cs.SOC), information retrieval (cs.IR), natural language processing (cs.CL), and cybersecurity (cs.CYBER).
